    "created_at": "2016-09-02T13:49:54Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-02T13:49:54Z",
    "body": "I'm working on a Laptop with an additional display. That display is set `primary` in the system-settings of Linux Mint. Unless I turn it off, my app always shows up on the display of the laptop. So I always have to move it over to my \"working display\". :angry:\n\nIt would be great to detect the active display and add it as a parameter to the constructor of BrowserWindow.\n"
